<title>JAPAN: Takefuji shares down on reported lawsuit.</title>
<headline>Takefuji shares down on reported lawsuit.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in consumer loan company Takefuji Corp slid on the over-the-counter market on Thursday, depressed by reports that a political group had filed a lawsuit against it, traders said.</p>
<p>At 0554 GMT, the share price stood at 5,900 yen, down 120 yen from its Wednesday close.  </p>
<p>Japanese daily Sankei Shimbun said on Thursday that a Shizuoka-based political group had sued Takefuji seeking payment of three billion yen that the group said Takefuji had promised.</p>
<p>A Takefuji spokesman said the lawsuit was groundless and the company would contest it in court.</p>
